Was it habit merely that made most women in 
dorse their husbands so energetically ? Or was it 
from that strained endeavor of loyalty, an exalted 



 

feeling of duty, and a secret mortification lest the 
world should see the feet of clay on which their 
idol supported himself? She had always felt she 
must be really proud of her husband. It was one 
of the articles of faith with the new woman that 
she did not look at man through the eyes of the 
trained devotee, that she could weigh and measure 
according to an impartial standard, that she judged 
according to the real values and not the glamour 
